      "author": "auditadmin",
      "body_md": "# Security Audit Toolkit — Release Notes\n\nSuite release: **2026.1** · Product version: **1.0.4** · Channel: GA\n\n## About this release\n\n1.0.4 is a suite version-alignment release. All six AuditToolkit suite products are advanced\ntogether to a common **1.0.4** baseline so the suite ships as one coordinated release. There are\nno breaking changes; upgrade in place via the native package.\n\n## What's new in 1.0.4\n\n- **Unified suite versioning.** All six suite products — Audit Tool, CMDB API Data Collection,\n  Asset Command Centre, Linux Security Lite, Switch Exposure Center, and Audit Assurance Node —\n  are aligned at 1.0.4, replacing the previous mixed 1.0.2 / 1.0.3 lines.\n- **Consistent licensing and legal.** The shared End User License Agreement, Liability Disclaimer\n  and Indemnity, Copyright, and Licensing documents apply uniformly across the suite and are\n  bundled with this product.\n- **Documentation references official channels only.** The customer documentation references only\n  the official AuditToolkit website and public release channel — no private source-control hosts.\n  Internal cross-references were verified and the documents bundle is checked against its signed\n  manifest.\n- **Carries forward the 1.0.3 documentation-accuracy pass** (deployment described as native\n  `.deb`/`.rpm` with PostgreSQL auto-provisioned; in-product Documents page ships in the packages).\n\n## Install, upgrade and support\n\n- Installation and upgrade: see `CUSTOMER-DEPLOYMENT-PACK.md` (install/upgrade the native\n  `.deb`/`.rpm`; the package runs database migrations on upgrade).\n- Day-2 operations and issue resolution: see the Operations Runbook and Troubleshooting Guide.\n- Licensing and legal terms: see the Licensing and Legal documents in this set.\n\n## Version alignment\n\n- Suite: `2026.1` · Product (Audit Tool): `1.0.4` · Channel: GA.\n- All six suite products are released together at 1.0.4.\n",
