      "body_md": "Audit Tool **1.0.3** — GA (suite 2026.1).\n\n### Server + agents\n- **Linux** — server + fleet/standalone/hypervisor agents as `.deb` + `.rpm` (self-contained: bundled python3.12 wheelhouse, systemd units, customer-docs). In-place update bundles: `application`/`audits` tarballs.\n- **Windows** — fleet/standalone/hypervisor agents as `.msi` (embedded Python).\n\n`SHA256SUMS-1.0.3.txt` covers every artifact. See `README.md` / `CHANGELOG.md`.\n\n### Signing\n- **Linux** packages are signed via the AuditToolkit Release Signing key.\n- **Windows MSIs** are Authenticode-signed (SHA-256, timestamped) with the internal AuditToolkit code-signing certificate. A publicly-trusted OV/EV certificate / Azure Trusted Signing identity is not currently available, so Windows may show an \"unknown publisher\" prompt — a known signing-infrastructure limitation, **not** a release blocker.\n\n### Post-GA follow-ups (non-blocking)\n- Hypervisor agent is built at 1.0.3 while its `version.py` reads 0.1.0 (separate product — reconcile).\n- The oversized `full.tar.gz` update bundle is omitted pending a `build-release.sh` exclude fix; the deb/rpm are the canonical full installs.",
